<ul>
 <li><a href="http://www.lungusa2.org/slati/reports/CollegeSmokingTrendReport-Embargoed.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>Big Tobacco on Campus: Ending the Addiction â€“ September&nbsp;2008</strong></a><br />
  This trend alert examines the issue of smoking on college campuses, tobacco industry marketing to college students and policies that colleges can put into place to stop this.</li>
 <li><a href="http://www.lungusa2.org/slati/reports/Trend%20Alert_Waterpipes.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>An Emerging Deadly Trend - Waterpipe Tobacco Use - February&nbsp;2007</strong></a><br />
  This trend alert looks at the science behind hookah tobacco use, a relatively new tobacco use trend in the United States, and seeks to correct the misperception that hookah tobacco use is&nbsp;harmless.</li>
 <li><a href="http://www.lungusa2.org/slati/reports/CandyFlavoredUpdatedAlert.pdf" target="_blank"><strong>From Joe Camel to Kauai Kolada - The Marketing of Candy - Flavored Cigarettes- May 2006</strong></a><br />
  This trend alert summarizes the history of different flavorings in cigarettes, provides evidence of how these new types of cigarettes appeal to youth, and describes state and federal efforts to prohibit their sale.</li>
 <li><a href="http://www.lungusa2.org/slati/appendixe.php"><strong>Laws that Prevent Stronger Local Tobacco Control Laws </strong></a><strong><br />
 </strong>Some states keep local communities from passing tougher tobacco control laws. Is your state one of them?</li>
 <li><a href="http://www.lungusa2.org/slati/appendixf.php"><strong>State &ldquo;Smoker Protection&rdquo; Laws<br />
 </strong></a>Lists state laws that elevate smokers to a protected class.</li>
</ul>
